OverTheWire Bandit – Level 27 → Level 28 

Level Goal
A git repository is hosted at:
ssh://bandit27-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org/home/bandit27-git/repo
using port 2220.
The password for user bandit27-git is the same as the password for bandit27.

Commands Used
git clone
ls
cat

Steps
SSH into the Bandit server as usual.
Use the bandit27 password to SSH into the git user:
   ssh bandit27-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
Clone the repository located at /home/bandit27-git/repo:
   git clone ssh://bandit27-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org:2220/home/bandit27-git/repo
Change into the cloned repository directory:
   cd repo
List the files and inspect their contents to find the password for bandit28:
  ls -la
  cat <file-containing-password>

Result
The password for bandit28 was found inside the cloned git repository.

What I Learned
How to connect to remote git repositories over SSH on non-standard ports.
Basic git commands to clone and explore repositories.
The importance of exploring hidden or unusual files in security challenges.
